sentences: Cristina Pato Lorenzo (born August 17, 1980) is a Galician bagpiper, pianist and composer.
In 2017 she was collaborating with Harvard University as one of its Blodgett Distinguished Artists in Residence.

She appeared on the Grammy Award-winning albums Yo-Yo Ma and Friends: Songs of Joy and Peace (2008) and Sing Me Home (2016) and in the documentary The Music of Strangers: Yo-Yo Ma and The Silk Road Ensemble, directed by academy award winner Morgan Neville.
